=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
        POKER HAND RANKINGS
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
Hands are ranked from strongest (#1) to weakest (#10).


------------------------------------
1.  ROYAL FLUSH (Strongest Hand)
------------------------------------
A♦ K♦ Q♦ J♦ 10♦ (all same suit)
The highest possible straight flush.

------------------------------------
2.  STRAIGHT FLUSH
------------------------------------
Five consecutive cards all in the same suit.
Example: 9♣ 8♣ 7♣ 6♣ 5♣

------------------------------------
3.  FOUR OF A KIND
------------------------------------
Four cards of the same rank.
Example: Q♠ Q♥ Q♣ Q♦ + any fifth card

------------------------------------
4.  FULL HOUSE
------------------------------------
Three cards of one rank + two cards of another rank.
Example: J♣ J♦ J♠ + 4♣ 4♠

------------------------------------
5.  FLUSH
------------------------------------
Five cards of the same suit, not in sequence.
Example: A♥ 9♥ 7♥ 5♥ 2♥

------------------------------------
6.  STRAIGHT
------------------------------------
Five cards in sequence, mixed suits.
Example: 10♠ 9♦ 8♥ 7♣ 6♣

Special case:
A-2-3-4-5 is the lowest straight (called the "wheel").

------------------------------------
7.  THREE OF A KIND
------------------------------------
Three cards of the same rank.
Example: 7♦ 7♣ 7♠ + two unrelated cards

------------------------------------
8.  TWO PAIR
------------------------------------
Two different pairs + one extra card.
Example: K♠ K♦ + 9♣ 9♠ + 3♥

------------------------------------
9.  ONE PAIR
------------------------------------
Two cards of the same rank + three other cards.
Example: 5♣ 5♦ + 10♠ 8♣ 2♥

------------------------------------
10. HIGH CARD (Weakest Hand)
------------------------------------
No matching ranks, no straight, no flush.
Best card determines the winner.
Example: A♣ 10♦ 7♠ 4♥ 2♣ (Ace-high)
